Reasoning: The paper focuses on localization for autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of occupancy grid maps and ray casting suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may also be relevant sub-categories. The use of a particle filter for localization suggests machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant. Finally, the fact that the algorithm is designed to run on resource-constrained mobile robots suggests systems and control (cs.SY) may also be a relevant sub-category.
